1
00:00:03,705 --> 00:00:04,673
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:04,673 --> 00:00:06,074
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,074 --> 00:00:07,142
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:08,810 --> 00:00:12,481
So this is a report from the National
Agricultural Science and Technology?

5
00:00:13,882 --> 00:00:16,218
It's a soil sample analysis report.

6
00:00:18,587 --> 00:00:19,454
Let's open it.

7
00:00:30,365 --> 00:00:32,367
Man, this looks complicated.

8
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:36,738
So what does it say?

9
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:42,277
This...

10
00:00:42,978 --> 00:00:46,214
is not an external invasive organism.

11
00:00:47,382 --> 00:00:49,885
So that means no one deliberately
spread it?

12
00:00:50,419 --> 00:00:51,353
That's right.

13
00:00:53,355 --> 00:00:55,524
It's a native microbial population...

14
00:00:55,524 --> 00:00:58,060
commonly found in local soil.

15
00:00:59,594 --> 00:01:00,629
So...

16
00:01:01,630 --> 00:01:03,365
that means it was already in Yeonri-ri
to begin with?

17
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:06,501
Yes. Under normal conditions,
it stays inactive.

18
00:01:06,902 --> 00:01:09,338
But under certain
environmental conditions,

19
00:01:09,338 --> 00:01:11,673
it rapidly multiplies.

20
00:01:12,908 --> 00:01:15,310
So, something about the soil
in Yeonri-ri changed?

21
00:01:15,877 --> 00:01:17,679
It wasn't a natural change,

22
00:01:18,146 --> 00:01:20,982
but an artificially altered
environmental condition.

23
00:01:21,516 --> 00:01:23,819
For it to spread across
the entire village,

24
00:01:23,819 --> 00:01:25,787
it would have to be a pretty major change.

25
00:01:35,564 --> 00:01:37,065
I'm telling Mom.

26
00:01:37,065 --> 00:01:38,667
Go ahead.

27
00:01:40,068 --> 00:01:41,870
That tickles. Stop.

28
00:01:43,739 --> 00:01:44,740
Is anyone home?

29
00:01:45,907 --> 00:01:47,075
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

30
00:01:47,075 --> 00:01:47,976
Yes?

31
00:01:48,677 --> 00:01:49,978
Is Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo home?

32
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,914
Registered mail delivery.

33
00:01:58,253 --> 00:01:59,121
Okay.

34
00:02:00,555 --> 00:02:02,024
Yes, that's me.

35
00:02:02,024 --> 00:02:04,092
You are Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo, correct?

36
00:02:04,926 --> 00:02:06,495
This is a special court delivery.

37
00:02:07,596 --> 00:02:09,564
Please sign here.

38
00:02:10,632 --> 00:02:12,067
From the court to me?

39
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:12,934
Yes, right here.

40
00:02:23,512 --> 00:02:24,413
Here you go.

41
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,181
Goodbye.

42
00:02:34,056 --> 00:02:36,992
A lawsuit to recover a loan?

43
00:02:37,459 --> 00:02:38,660
Where are you?

44
00:02:39,394 --> 00:02:41,263
Pay me back, you wench.

45
00:02:49,037 --> 00:02:51,807
You thought I wouldn't find you?

46
00:02:53,842 --> 00:02:56,611
You thought hiding in some rural town
in Korea would keep me from finding you?

47
00:03:14,229 --> 00:03:15,864
What's this? It's registered mail.

48
00:03:15,864 --> 00:03:18,467
- Is it for me?
- No, give it back.

49
00:03:35,617 --> 00:03:36,718
Is it for you?

50
00:03:37,652 --> 00:03:38,687
No.

51
00:03:41,056 --> 00:03:41,990
This...

52
00:03:43,158 --> 00:03:45,160
is study material for Ji Gu's class.

53
00:03:48,964 --> 00:03:51,299
They send things like that in the mail
these days?

54
00:03:51,299 --> 00:03:52,300
Yes,

55
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,136
since it can't be leaked carelessly.

56
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:56,872
You don't need to worry about it.

57
00:04:15,524 --> 00:04:17,759
(EP10)

58
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:24,700
(Before the Soil Dries, The Miracle Fades)

59
00:04:38,714 --> 00:04:40,549
Wow, this is crazy.

60
00:04:40,549 --> 00:04:42,050
Dad, look at this.

61
00:04:42,684 --> 00:04:45,387
Wow. Are these the peas
you planted at school?

62
00:04:45,787 --> 00:04:47,222
They've grown a lot.

63
00:04:55,130 --> 00:04:57,466
You two will be harvesting these soon.

64
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,569
Even the sprouts look like you two.
Older and younger brothers.

65
00:05:01,303 --> 00:05:02,304
Dad.

66
00:05:03,438 --> 00:05:05,574
I think I've got a talent for farming.

67
00:05:06,441 --> 00:05:09,411
Peas sprout quickly in the early stages,

68
00:05:09,411 --> 00:05:11,613
so anyone can grow them this much.

69
00:05:11,847 --> 00:05:13,949
Seong Ji Gu. Are you jealous?

70
00:05:13,949 --> 00:05:15,384
Because mine's way bigger than yours?

71
00:05:16,084 --> 00:05:17,352
It's not about height.

72
00:05:17,352 --> 00:05:19,588
The stem needs to be strong
to last longer.

73
00:05:21,089 --> 00:05:23,825
Should we give it nutrients or something?

74
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:24,793
Yes.

75
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,329
Dad, I want books.

76
00:05:27,329 --> 00:05:30,165
Get me every book
from growth conditions...

77
00:05:30,165 --> 00:05:32,734
to pests on peas.

78
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:41,376
Ji Gu. Reading books alone
won't make the peas grow.

79
00:05:54,189 --> 00:05:56,224
(Complaint)

80
00:05:57,793 --> 00:05:59,361
(Amount 30,000 dollars)

81
00:05:59,361 --> 00:06:00,462
In two weeks,

82
00:06:01,263 --> 00:06:02,330
I have to pay back this amount?

83
00:06:03,432 --> 00:06:04,399
What do I do?

84
00:06:05,367 --> 00:06:06,835
Unbelievable.

85
00:06:14,209 --> 00:06:16,044
I know where you are.

86
00:06:16,044 --> 00:06:17,779
Don't even think about running,
and pay up.

87
00:06:18,647 --> 00:06:20,682
If you don't, be ready to go to jail.

88
00:06:24,553 --> 00:06:25,854
(Delete)

89
00:06:27,622 --> 00:06:30,359
Honey, I just need to start
the rice cooker?

90
00:06:32,027 --> 00:06:33,328
Well...

91
00:06:33,328 --> 00:06:34,763
I'll do it.

92
00:06:35,230 --> 00:06:36,431
Just wait.

93
00:06:45,207 --> 00:06:48,143
Honey, nothing's wrong, is it?

94
00:06:48,143 --> 00:06:50,078
- I'll be right there.
- Do I just press start?

95
00:06:50,078 --> 00:06:51,213
Hold on.

96
00:07:12,801 --> 00:07:14,703
The aroma is sweet and nice, right?

97
00:07:14,703 --> 00:07:15,537
Yes.

98
00:07:16,004 --> 00:07:16,972
The apples...

99
00:07:17,806 --> 00:07:20,275
are really red and beautiful.

100
00:07:23,345 --> 00:07:25,681
These are Gamhong apples...

101
00:07:25,681 --> 00:07:28,083
from the orchard we visited before.

102
00:07:29,284 --> 00:07:31,720
They have such a beautiful color,

103
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,623
so they look great on tarts or cakes.

104
00:07:34,623 --> 00:07:35,757
They taste great too.

105
00:07:36,892 --> 00:07:37,693
No wonder.

106
00:07:43,498 --> 00:07:46,201
Gamhong apples taste good
even with the skin on.

107
00:07:49,371 --> 00:07:50,339
You're just cutting apples.

108
00:07:50,339 --> 00:07:52,107
Do you really need to be this close?

109
00:07:53,909 --> 00:07:55,911
Dad, don't you have anything better to do?

110
00:07:55,911 --> 00:07:58,513
I've got plenty to do. Keeping an eye
on you is my job.

111
00:07:58,513 --> 00:07:59,881
What do you mean?

112
00:07:59,881 --> 00:08:01,650
We're in the middle of developing
a new menu.

113
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:03,218
- Right?
- Right.

114
00:08:03,752 --> 00:08:05,887
I heard you like sweets.

115
00:08:06,788 --> 00:08:09,925
We're trying to make a sweet dessert
using apples.

116
00:08:11,526 --> 00:08:15,330
You're so scrawny and pale.

117
00:08:15,330 --> 00:08:18,333
If only you were big and solid
like some people.

118
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,268
Dad, Ji Cheon is such a solid,
dependable person.

119
00:08:20,268 --> 00:08:22,204
What do you know?

120
00:08:24,039 --> 00:08:26,575
I'm home.

121
00:08:27,776 --> 00:08:29,611
My deer is home.

122
00:08:29,611 --> 00:08:31,747
My lovely deer, have some apples.

123
00:08:31,747 --> 00:08:32,647
Thanks.

124
00:08:36,651 --> 00:08:37,552
Is it good?

125
00:08:38,286 --> 00:08:39,154
It's sweet.

126
00:08:40,355 --> 00:08:42,157
You're on my side, right?

127
00:08:43,091 --> 00:08:45,527
But what are you doing here
while they are working?

128
00:08:45,527 --> 00:08:46,828
Come to our room right now.

129
00:08:47,829 --> 00:08:49,031
Go home now.

130
00:08:50,899 --> 00:08:52,234
Stop smiling and go.

131
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:53,568
You think being handsome is enough?

132
00:08:54,036 --> 00:08:57,039
Keep working on those sweet recipes.

133
00:08:57,039 --> 00:08:58,607
- Go. Hurry.
- Let's go to our room now.

134
00:08:58,607 --> 00:09:00,976
- You think being handsome is enough?
- Why do you care?

135
00:09:00,976 --> 00:09:01,843
Rest well.

136
00:09:15,023 --> 00:09:17,359
Give it to me. I'll do it.

137
00:09:17,359 --> 00:09:20,495
You see how well I folded these?

138
00:09:21,296 --> 00:09:23,765
I've been an expert on folding clothes...

139
00:09:23,765 --> 00:09:25,634
since I was in the army.

140
00:09:26,902 --> 00:09:30,205
You went through a lot while I was gone.

141
00:09:33,175 --> 00:09:36,078
While you were gone, I finally realized...

142
00:09:36,078 --> 00:09:37,479
that the word "wife" comes from...

143
00:09:37,479 --> 00:09:39,848
the meaning of "the sun of a household."

144
00:09:41,717 --> 00:09:44,653
Without you, the warmth in the house
was gone.

145
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:46,755
It didn't feel like our home anymore.

146
00:09:48,623 --> 00:09:50,425
It's all talk.

147
00:09:50,425 --> 00:09:51,626
Not at all.

148
00:09:52,494 --> 00:09:54,396
I want us to do everything together now.

149
00:09:54,396 --> 00:09:56,231
Housework and the kids.

150
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:00,435
You know cabbage seedlings?

151
00:10:01,203 --> 00:10:04,573
If you plant one only,
even a small gust can break it.

152
00:10:04,573 --> 00:10:07,075
That's why you must plant them
in pairs, side by side.

153
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:10,178
It's the same with a married couple.

154
00:10:10,946 --> 00:10:12,881
Things that are too heavy
to carry alone...

155
00:10:12,881 --> 00:10:15,283
are manageable
when you carry them together.

156
00:10:21,123 --> 00:10:22,324
Whether it's about Ji Cheon...

157
00:10:23,658 --> 00:10:25,894
or something else I don't know about,

158
00:10:27,329 --> 00:10:29,498
don't carry it alone anymore.

159
00:10:30,332 --> 00:10:31,099
Okay?

160
00:10:43,478 --> 00:10:44,346
Honey.

161
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,014
Honey.

162
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,918
I'm your husband.

163
00:10:50,485 --> 00:10:51,887
If anything gets too hard,

164
00:10:51,887 --> 00:10:53,655
let me know everything, okay?

165
00:10:56,692 --> 00:10:57,659
Okay.

166
00:10:58,593 --> 00:11:01,396
There's nothing wrong.
I'm just a bit tired.

167
00:11:02,464 --> 00:11:03,532
You're tired?

168
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:05,233
Yes.

169
00:11:05,634 --> 00:11:06,535
I'm fine.

170
00:11:15,777 --> 00:11:16,712
(Mat Story)

171
00:11:16,712 --> 00:11:18,980
An unidentified fungal outbreak?

172
00:11:20,415 --> 00:11:22,317
They say farming depends on god.

173
00:11:22,851 --> 00:11:25,053
It seems god is really helping us
this time.

174
00:11:28,724 --> 00:11:31,493
There's no better excuse
than a natural disaster.

175
00:11:32,094 --> 00:11:34,896
Keep a close eye on Manager Seong Tae Hun.

176
00:11:35,664 --> 00:11:37,833
What's Seong Tae Hun going to find...

177
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,602
just by looking through a microscope?

178
00:11:40,969 --> 00:11:42,204
The land is dying.

179
00:11:42,204 --> 00:11:44,373
What could he possibly do
to save the land?

180
00:11:44,373 --> 00:11:47,175
That punk. All he has is his height.

181
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:52,647
I'm sorry.

182
00:11:54,549 --> 00:11:56,785
You can't leave things up to god only.

183
00:11:58,453 --> 00:12:00,255
If something goes wrong later,

184
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:04,326
god won't protect you too.

185
00:12:05,293 --> 00:12:07,662
I'm not sure what you mean.

186
00:12:08,330 --> 00:12:10,332
I've been loyal to you this whole time...

187
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,201
Keep a close eye on Seong Tae Hun.

188
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:17,105
And don't think your position...

189
00:12:17,105 --> 00:12:18,507
is any safer than his.

190
00:12:21,309 --> 00:12:22,144
Yes, sir.

191
00:12:30,452 --> 00:12:31,520
Seong Tae Hun.

192
00:12:32,421 --> 00:12:34,423
(Yeonri-ri)

193
00:12:34,423 --> 00:12:37,092
There's such a thing as a jinx.

194
00:12:37,092 --> 00:12:38,593
Don't city people know that?

195
00:12:38,994 --> 00:12:42,664
Chief, have you teamed up...

196
00:12:42,664 --> 00:12:44,633
with that Mat Story lackey now?

197
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:46,435
What are you talking about?

198
00:12:47,469 --> 00:12:49,404
Can't you see that...

199
00:12:49,404 --> 00:12:52,774
I'm working day and night for Yeonri-ri?

200
00:12:52,774 --> 00:12:55,510
Just let me know if you need any help.

201
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:56,845
I'll join you.

202
00:12:57,145 --> 00:12:58,947
Has anything...

203
00:12:58,947 --> 00:13:01,783
changed in Yeonri-ri
compared to last year?

204
00:13:01,783 --> 00:13:04,619
Even small things are fine.
Please tell me everything.

205
00:13:05,153 --> 00:13:06,088
Yes.

206
00:13:08,223 --> 00:13:11,693
There was something really shocking.

207
00:13:12,594 --> 00:13:14,663
Yes, that did happen.

208
00:13:14,663 --> 00:13:15,831
What is it?

209
00:13:15,831 --> 00:13:17,265
Did the soil temperature change?

210
00:13:17,265 --> 00:13:18,633
Or maybe the groundwater level...

211
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:20,602
You know that house with a persimmon tree
in the back hill?

212
00:13:21,737 --> 00:13:22,738
Pardon?

213
00:13:24,306 --> 00:13:26,742
Have you noticed anything unusual...

214
00:13:26,742 --> 00:13:28,110
around Yeonri-ri lately?

215
00:13:30,746 --> 00:13:31,747
Could that be it?

216
00:13:31,747 --> 00:13:34,116
What is it? Tell me.

217
00:13:34,116 --> 00:13:36,885
The cow at the house with a persimmon tree
in the back hill...

218
00:13:36,885 --> 00:13:38,153
had twins.

219
00:13:39,187 --> 00:13:40,555
They even handed out rice cakes.

220
00:13:42,891 --> 00:13:44,159
Twins?

221
00:13:45,794 --> 00:13:49,431
Is this about their cow having twins?

222
00:13:49,431 --> 00:13:50,332
Yes.

223
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:54,102
He doesn't understand how special that is.

224
00:13:55,337 --> 00:13:56,571
Then...

225
00:13:57,406 --> 00:13:58,940
Yes, Cheon Ji's place.

226
00:13:59,441 --> 00:14:00,342
Cheon Ji's place?

227
00:14:00,342 --> 00:14:02,310
- Yes, their hen.
- Yes?

228
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:03,612
That hen...

229
00:14:03,845 --> 00:14:06,515
lays three eggs a day.

230
00:14:06,515 --> 00:14:07,683
- For real?
- Yes.

231
00:14:11,253 --> 00:14:12,254
So...

232
00:14:18,493 --> 00:14:19,394
You're headed somewhere?

233
00:14:19,961 --> 00:14:21,329
I just want to be alone.

234
00:14:24,766 --> 00:14:29,471
That man coming here
was the biggest change here.

235
00:14:52,327 --> 00:14:55,430
But if you blend pumpkin only,
isn't it too thick and heavy?

236
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:57,232
Yes, it is a bit thick,

237
00:14:57,232 --> 00:14:59,101
but I intentionally reduced the sweetness.

238
00:14:59,434 --> 00:15:02,137
Our drinks are all based
on healthy recipes.

239
00:15:04,539 --> 00:15:07,175
My mom used to be really sick.

240
00:15:13,382 --> 00:15:14,816
I see.

241
00:15:14,816 --> 00:15:16,251
But she's okay now.

242
00:15:17,085 --> 00:15:19,921
She went through cancer treatment before.

243
00:15:19,921 --> 00:15:22,624
During chemotherapy, your mouth gets sore,

244
00:15:22,624 --> 00:15:24,326
so you can't really eat anything else.
It stings.

245
00:15:26,094 --> 00:15:27,029
I see.

246
00:15:35,837 --> 00:15:37,239
(Cinnamon powder)

247
00:15:41,076 --> 00:15:42,577
What if we add a bit of this?

248
00:15:52,688 --> 00:15:54,056
The aftertaste is clean.

249
00:15:54,690 --> 00:15:57,125
And it really cuts through the heaviness.

250
00:15:57,125 --> 00:15:59,661
Cinnamon also helps with bloating...

251
00:15:59,661 --> 00:16:00,962
and digestion.

252
00:16:02,264 --> 00:16:04,333
It might be good to add turmeric too.

253
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:06,234
It gives a nice yellow color...

254
00:16:07,002 --> 00:16:08,403
and has anti-inflammatory benefits.

255
00:16:10,238 --> 00:16:12,974
We don't have turmeric here,
but I have some at home.

256
00:16:12,974 --> 00:16:14,843
Do you want to try making it
together later?

257
00:16:23,085 --> 00:16:24,386
My goodness.

258
00:16:26,421 --> 00:16:28,690
What is this smell?

259
00:16:28,690 --> 00:16:30,592
I smell something beautiful.

260
00:16:31,193 --> 00:16:33,395
The flower of youth is blooming in full.

261
00:16:34,996 --> 00:16:35,964
Look, Hye Sun.

262
00:16:36,732 --> 00:16:37,799
I don't know anything.

263
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:39,868
What's blooming?

264
00:16:39,868 --> 00:16:41,803
What are you talking about?

265
00:16:43,105 --> 00:16:45,040
I didn't see anything.

266
00:16:45,807 --> 00:16:48,443
Right. I didn't see anything,

267
00:16:48,443 --> 00:16:50,212
so I don't know anything.

268
00:16:50,212 --> 00:16:52,314
I don't know anything.

269
00:16:52,314 --> 00:16:56,251
My goodness. Mi Ryeo ran away from home,
and you shared a few meals together.

270
00:16:56,251 --> 00:16:57,185
So...

271
00:16:57,819 --> 00:17:00,288
you've gotten attached now?

272
00:17:02,124 --> 00:17:03,325
It tastes okay, right?

273
00:17:03,325 --> 00:17:04,493
Yes, I think it's good.

274
00:17:13,135 --> 00:17:14,036
Here.

275
00:17:14,336 --> 00:17:16,004
Take just one sip each.

276
00:17:16,004 --> 00:17:17,606
I put a lot of effort into making this.

277
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,941
Why does it look like this?

278
00:17:22,444 --> 00:17:23,545
Are you trying to kill me?

279
00:17:29,084 --> 00:17:30,952
Ji Cheon, is this apple juice?

280
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,621
Apple?

281
00:17:34,022 --> 00:17:35,023
Is it an Aori apple?

282
00:17:39,394 --> 00:17:40,295
Come on.

283
00:17:40,829 --> 00:17:42,531
You loaded this with sugar.

284
00:17:43,298 --> 00:17:46,201
Hey. There's spinach and carrots
that you hate the most.

285
00:17:46,535 --> 00:17:48,804
Give me some more.

286
00:17:48,804 --> 00:17:49,538
More?

287
00:17:51,540 --> 00:17:52,507
Carrots?

288
00:18:06,588 --> 00:18:09,224
Something in the environment
that changed suddenly...

289
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,729
The beginning is what matters most.

290
00:18:16,598 --> 00:18:19,167
Let's go back and re-examine everything
step by step.

291
00:18:25,774 --> 00:18:27,743
Let's look carefully.

292
00:18:27,743 --> 00:18:28,877
What changed?

293
00:18:28,877 --> 00:18:30,912
Just wait until I find it.

294
00:18:40,188 --> 00:18:43,125
Nothing seems to have changed
in the past few days.

295
00:18:45,427 --> 00:18:47,129
The soil in the village seems fine.

296
00:18:50,332 --> 00:18:51,633
What could it be?

297
00:18:53,702 --> 00:18:54,770
What's the source of the problem?

298
00:19:03,545 --> 00:19:04,646
Mom.

299
00:19:04,646 --> 00:19:05,614
Mother.

300
00:19:06,314 --> 00:19:09,284
Maybe I should quit studying...

301
00:19:09,284 --> 00:19:10,452
and just become a farmer.

302
00:19:11,353 --> 00:19:12,821
There's not that much difference...

303
00:19:13,622 --> 00:19:14,623
between studying and farming.

304
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:20,629
Don't think of them as your kids.

305
00:19:21,396 --> 00:19:23,498
Think of them as boarders.

306
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:26,468
It's easier that way.

307
00:19:28,503 --> 00:19:29,371
Sure.

308
00:19:29,871 --> 00:19:33,508
If that's what you want to do,
that's good.

309
00:19:35,477 --> 00:19:36,478
What?

310
00:19:36,812 --> 00:19:38,947
Mom, did you hear me?

311
00:19:38,947 --> 00:19:40,916
I said I want to be a farmer
instead of studying.

312
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:44,586
Yes, I heard you. That's fine too.

313
00:19:45,854 --> 00:19:50,492
But take your time thinking
about your future.

314
00:19:50,492 --> 00:19:53,328
Should I ask Dad for a field of my own?

315
00:19:54,162 --> 00:19:55,764
These days, smart farming is the trend.

316
00:19:56,064 --> 00:19:58,600
You can just press buttons
on your phone like a game.

317
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,302
Then water comes out,
and temperature adjusts...

318
00:20:00,802 --> 00:20:03,505
It's insanely easy.

319
00:20:03,905 --> 00:20:05,774
You can learn how to be a farmer
on YouTube.

320
00:20:06,308 --> 00:20:07,642
You little...

321
00:20:07,642 --> 00:20:09,011
Seong Ji Sang.

322
00:20:09,011 --> 00:20:09,878
What?

323
00:20:09,878 --> 00:20:12,981
What?

324
00:20:12,981 --> 00:20:15,350
Why are you suddenly talking about
becoming a farmer?

325
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:17,452
What on earth is going on
in that head of yours?

326
00:20:18,587 --> 00:20:20,655
- You make me so angry! Hey!
- What?

327
00:20:20,655 --> 00:20:22,524
- Why you little...
- What?

328
00:20:22,524 --> 00:20:24,192
Hey.

329
00:20:24,192 --> 00:20:25,861
- Don't come near me.
- Stop right there.

330
00:20:27,396 --> 00:20:28,330
Seong Ji Sang.

331
00:20:29,031 --> 00:20:31,099
I told you to do your homework.
Why are you tagging along?

332
00:20:31,466 --> 00:20:32,601
Mom.

333
00:20:32,601 --> 00:20:35,003
It's because he has a girlfriend.

334
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:36,204
What?

335
00:20:36,204 --> 00:20:39,074
He's tagging along,
hoping to run into her.

336
00:20:39,608 --> 00:20:40,509
Right?

337
00:20:41,877 --> 00:20:42,944
That's not it.

338
00:20:45,714 --> 00:20:48,984
You're speaking of a girlfriend
in Korea as well?

339
00:20:48,984 --> 00:20:50,752
What will you become when you grow up?

340
00:20:51,687 --> 00:20:53,789
I told you. A farmer.

341
00:20:56,758 --> 00:20:58,427
You think farming is easy?

342
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:01,029
Farmers need to study
and know their stuff too.

343
00:21:03,298 --> 00:21:04,366
Why do you always yell at me?

344
00:21:04,366 --> 00:21:06,768
He's so immature.

345
00:21:06,768 --> 00:21:07,803
Right?

346
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:09,905
What's your dream?

347
00:21:11,973 --> 00:21:12,941
My dream?

348
00:21:17,713 --> 00:21:18,647
For you...

349
00:21:19,648 --> 00:21:21,350
to grow up healthy...

350
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:22,684
and become good people.

351
00:21:23,251 --> 00:21:24,319
No.

352
00:21:24,853 --> 00:21:26,521
That's our dream.

353
00:21:26,521 --> 00:21:27,656
I meant your dream.

354
00:21:28,156 --> 00:21:29,658
Don't you have one?

355
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:39,801
I used to.

356
00:21:41,837 --> 00:21:42,804
But...

357
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:47,676
it's been so long, so...

358
00:21:49,778 --> 00:21:53,015
I don't know.

359
00:21:55,350 --> 00:21:58,353
Then you can start thinking about it now.

360
00:21:58,787 --> 00:21:59,921
Now?

361
00:22:00,555 --> 00:22:01,356
Yes.

362
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:03,291
Ji Sang wants to be a farmer,

363
00:22:06,028 --> 00:22:08,230
and I want to be a scientist.

364
00:22:09,464 --> 00:22:12,100
If you start now,

365
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,136
you can achieve your dream later too.

366
00:22:18,607 --> 00:22:19,508
Yes.

367
00:22:24,012 --> 00:22:26,314
Thank you, son.

368
00:22:28,717 --> 00:22:29,651
All right.

369
00:22:31,019 --> 00:22:31,887
Let's go.

370
00:22:33,321 --> 00:22:34,222
Wait up.

371
00:22:39,461 --> 00:22:40,462
I don't get it.

372
00:22:40,829 --> 00:22:43,298
No matter how much I look,
I just can't figure it out.

373
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:47,069
There wasn't any additional fertilization,

374
00:22:47,069 --> 00:22:48,036
and it hasn't even rained.

375
00:22:50,038 --> 00:22:52,741
It's not pesticides,
and it's not temperature either.

376
00:22:55,077 --> 00:22:56,778
The fact that it's continuously
multiplying means...

377
00:22:56,778 --> 00:22:59,348
there has to be another cause.

378
00:22:59,348 --> 00:23:01,717
(No decrease in mycelial activity)

379
00:23:01,717 --> 00:23:03,985
What on earth is driving you?

380
00:23:06,321 --> 00:23:08,090
- Let's go.
- I'm hungry.

381
00:23:08,090 --> 00:23:09,725
My arm hurts.

382
00:23:09,725 --> 00:23:11,026
Hurry up.

383
00:23:12,194 --> 00:23:14,096
Why do I always have to do this stuff?

384
00:23:14,463 --> 00:23:17,132
- Come on. You're older. Right?
- Yes.

385
00:23:17,132 --> 00:23:19,434
I'm always the one carrying heavy stuff.

386
00:23:19,434 --> 00:23:21,436
Hurry up. Let's go
make something good to eat.

387
00:23:22,237 --> 00:23:23,472
What's for dinner?

388
00:23:23,472 --> 00:23:26,041
They live here, right? Try knocking.

389
00:23:26,041 --> 00:23:27,075
Knock?

390
00:23:29,678 --> 00:23:30,645
No one seems to be home, right?

391
00:23:34,916 --> 00:23:36,752
Mom, the tangerines. They're rolling away.

392
00:23:37,853 --> 00:23:39,021
What's wrong, Mom?

393
00:23:40,689 --> 00:23:41,890
- Mom.
- Boys.

394
00:23:42,557 --> 00:23:45,594
Hold on. Sit down.

395
00:23:45,594 --> 00:23:47,062
Didn't you hear something?

396
00:23:47,529 --> 00:23:48,663
Am I wrong?

397
00:23:48,663 --> 00:23:50,632
It sounded like a person's voice. No?

398
00:23:51,199 --> 00:23:52,200
Mom, the tangerines...

399
00:23:57,472 --> 00:23:58,607
I don't think anyone's home.

400
00:23:59,408 --> 00:24:00,242
Hold on.

401
00:24:02,711 --> 00:24:04,579
- Is someone out there?
- Mom.

402
00:24:10,318 --> 00:24:13,689
There's no one inside.

403
00:24:13,689 --> 00:24:15,223
Where did she go?

404
00:24:16,024 --> 00:24:16,958
What's going on there?

405
00:24:26,268 --> 00:24:28,103
What are you doing here?

406
00:24:31,707 --> 00:24:32,674
Well...

407
00:24:35,644 --> 00:24:36,745
Who is that woman over there?

408
00:24:37,245 --> 00:24:38,814
What is she staring at?

409
00:24:40,048 --> 00:24:41,983
Go stay at our place for now.

410
00:24:45,821 --> 00:24:47,089
- Let's go talk to her.
- Okay.

411
00:24:48,123 --> 00:24:50,659
Take your kids and go to my house.

412
00:24:52,127 --> 00:24:53,295
Let's go to the chief's house.

413
00:24:54,129 --> 00:24:56,298
Let's go. Hurry.

414
00:24:56,298 --> 00:24:57,666
Be careful.

415
00:24:57,666 --> 00:24:59,001
Who are you,

416
00:24:59,634 --> 00:25:02,904
and why are you loitering
in front of that house?

417
00:25:05,907 --> 00:25:09,311
The woman who lives here racked up
a huge amount of debt in Canada...

418
00:25:09,311 --> 00:25:11,113
and ran away in the middle of the night.

419
00:25:11,113 --> 00:25:13,181
She's a con artist...

420
00:25:13,448 --> 00:25:15,784
who scammed a bunch of moms and ran off.

421
00:25:15,784 --> 00:25:16,685
You know that?

422
00:25:18,286 --> 00:25:20,088
The two of you.

423
00:25:20,822 --> 00:25:23,658
Did you both lose half your tongues?

424
00:25:23,658 --> 00:25:26,695
Why are you speaking rudely
to someone you just met?

425
00:25:27,162 --> 00:25:28,897
You must live around here.

426
00:25:30,766 --> 00:25:32,034
You know the woman who lives here, right?

427
00:25:32,034 --> 00:25:33,101
Where is she?

428
00:25:36,438 --> 00:25:38,607
If you're here to collect a debt,

429
00:25:38,607 --> 00:25:41,843
handle it quietly by calling her.

430
00:25:41,843 --> 00:25:46,148
Why are you hanging around
someone else's neighborhood,

431
00:25:46,148 --> 00:25:49,785
someone else's house like this?

432
00:25:50,719 --> 00:25:54,156
No one lives here anymore,

433
00:25:54,456 --> 00:25:57,159
so just get lost.

434
00:25:57,159 --> 00:25:58,293
Excuse me, ma'am.

435
00:25:58,860 --> 00:26:01,029
Why are you behaving so uncivilized?

436
00:26:02,864 --> 00:26:05,067
Did you just push me?

437
00:26:05,067 --> 00:26:06,335
Did you just push me?

438
00:26:07,035 --> 00:26:09,304
That was a mistake. It was dangerous.

439
00:26:10,005 --> 00:26:14,543
You should leave now.

440
00:26:14,910 --> 00:26:18,213
If you stay any longer,
this won't end well.

441
00:26:18,213 --> 00:26:19,514
I don't think I can leave.

442
00:26:19,514 --> 00:26:21,083
My arm isn't moving.

443
00:26:21,083 --> 00:26:22,551
I think I should call the police.

444
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,722
What did you just say?

445
00:26:27,189 --> 00:26:28,790
What did you just say?

446
00:26:29,191 --> 00:26:31,793
I don't know what's going on,

447
00:26:31,793 --> 00:26:34,696
but in situations like this,
you fight with numbers.

448
00:26:34,696 --> 00:26:35,897
- Got it?
- Yes.

449
00:26:35,897 --> 00:26:38,934
I'd rather fight one-on-one.

450
00:26:43,105 --> 00:26:46,908
Shoo. Go away.

451
00:26:46,908 --> 00:26:48,276
Shoo.

452
00:26:48,276 --> 00:26:49,611
You heard that?

453
00:26:49,611 --> 00:26:54,816
This is how things work in Yeonri-ri.

454
00:26:54,816 --> 00:26:56,151
An eye for an eye.

455
00:26:56,151 --> 00:26:59,087
You get back what you give!

456
00:26:59,087 --> 00:27:02,357
Do you want to fight?

457
00:27:02,357 --> 00:27:03,225
Do you?

458
00:27:04,693 --> 00:27:06,028
Unbelievable.

459
00:27:07,229 --> 00:27:09,598
Hold on. This is ridiculous.

460
00:27:10,632 --> 00:27:11,867
I don't believe this.

461
00:27:11,867 --> 00:27:12,934
What's wrong with her?

462
00:27:14,069 --> 00:27:15,170
I'm so scared.

463
00:27:15,537 --> 00:27:16,638
Hey, Jessica.

464
00:27:16,638 --> 00:27:18,774
- Where are you going?
- Jessica.

465
00:27:20,676 --> 00:27:23,078
Come back here.

466
00:27:23,078 --> 00:27:24,312
Come back here.

467
00:27:24,312 --> 00:27:26,148
- Sisters.
- I'll just...

468
00:27:26,615 --> 00:27:29,051
- You got here too late.
- Did we? It's okay.

469
00:27:29,051 --> 00:27:30,686
I was scared.

470
00:27:30,686 --> 00:27:32,087
You got scared?

471
00:27:32,087 --> 00:27:34,923
- Don't worry.
- You've been through a lot.

472
00:27:54,976 --> 00:27:57,446
You haven't eaten dinner yet, right?

473
00:27:57,446 --> 00:28:00,082
I'll make you something real quick.
Just wait a bit.

474
00:28:14,529 --> 00:28:15,430
Hey.

475
00:28:16,865 --> 00:28:19,167
Are you breathing okay?

476
00:28:24,072 --> 00:28:25,107
Slowly.

477
00:28:25,841 --> 00:28:26,775
Slowly.

478
00:28:31,279 --> 00:28:33,982
What happened?

479
00:28:35,517 --> 00:28:36,518
My kids...

480
00:28:38,754 --> 00:28:41,189
I wanted to give them better education...

481
00:28:41,823 --> 00:28:43,358
so I got greedy.

482
00:28:46,061 --> 00:28:47,729
After going to Canada,

483
00:28:49,264 --> 00:28:52,501
I felt bad about asking my husband
for more money.

484
00:28:57,939 --> 00:28:59,041
Then...

485
00:28:59,975 --> 00:29:03,578
I was told there was a good opportunity
to invest the money.

486
00:29:03,578 --> 00:29:05,213
So I took on debt.

487
00:29:06,481 --> 00:29:09,084
But it was a scam.

488
00:29:09,551 --> 00:29:11,653
Those scums.

489
00:29:11,653 --> 00:29:14,256
Of all people, how could they scam you?

490
00:29:15,657 --> 00:29:16,625
Calm down.

491
00:29:19,027 --> 00:29:23,065
I never thought things would
get out of hand like this.

492
00:29:24,499 --> 00:29:26,535
In the parents' group,

493
00:29:27,369 --> 00:29:29,304
that scammer borrowed
even more money in my name...

494
00:29:30,305 --> 00:29:32,774
and ran off.

495
00:29:33,675 --> 00:29:36,578
Then they should be going after
that scammer.

496
00:29:36,578 --> 00:29:39,548
Why are they coming after
an innocent person?

497
00:29:41,283 --> 00:29:43,051
But it is true...

498
00:29:43,051 --> 00:29:46,088
that I borrowed money from them
and couldn't pay it back.

499
00:29:46,088 --> 00:29:47,055
Goodness.

500
00:29:49,224 --> 00:29:52,260
What are we going to do?

501
00:29:54,296 --> 00:29:55,330
Here.

502
00:29:55,731 --> 00:29:59,134
A lawsuit has already been filed.

503
00:30:00,102 --> 00:30:03,939
I could even be arrested for fraud.

504
00:30:08,844 --> 00:30:10,479
What are we going to do?

505
00:30:10,479 --> 00:30:11,580
Here.

506
00:30:14,316 --> 00:30:17,019
What are we going to do?

507
00:30:19,955 --> 00:30:23,191
Have you talked to your husband
about this?

508
00:30:28,196 --> 00:30:29,297
But this...

509
00:30:30,232 --> 00:30:31,299
I mean...

510
00:30:32,067 --> 00:30:34,036
I basically ran away
and came back to Korea.

511
00:30:36,338 --> 00:30:37,506
But my husband...

512
00:30:38,540 --> 00:30:40,375
was assigned to Yeonri-ri.

513
00:30:42,244 --> 00:30:44,546
He's trying so hard
just to hold everything together.

514
00:30:44,546 --> 00:30:46,415
How can I tell him?

515
00:30:49,518 --> 00:30:51,887
What am I going to do? I just want to die.

516
00:30:53,522 --> 00:30:54,923
That's nonsense.

517
00:30:54,923 --> 00:30:57,859
I'm sure there is a way out of this.

518
00:30:58,326 --> 00:31:00,562
What am I going to do now?

519
00:31:00,562 --> 00:31:02,931
I'm sure there's a way.

520
00:31:04,499 --> 00:31:05,701
You've been through a lot.

521
00:31:15,610 --> 00:31:17,646
Fifteen days since the fungus
was discovered.

522
00:31:17,646 --> 00:31:20,148
(Native microbial community,
not natural, artificial change)

523
00:31:20,148 --> 00:31:22,017
I still haven't found the cause.

524
00:31:43,205 --> 00:31:44,139
Wait.

525
00:31:57,552 --> 00:31:58,453
It's not here.

526
00:31:59,421 --> 00:32:00,355
It's not here.

527
00:32:04,159 --> 00:32:05,093
There's...

528
00:32:06,628 --> 00:32:07,496
no fungus.

529
00:32:08,363 --> 00:32:10,465
It's the same soil,
but there's no fungus in here.

530
00:32:20,475 --> 00:32:22,844
If this wall reduced the impact,

531
00:32:23,078 --> 00:32:26,748
then was something carried by the wind?

532
00:32:33,088 --> 00:32:35,590
(Yeonri-ri)

533
00:32:47,402 --> 00:32:48,737
As we get closer
to the neighboring village,

534
00:32:49,771 --> 00:32:51,239
the fungus clearly decreases.

535
00:32:55,644 --> 00:32:57,612
Why did it spread only in Yeonri-ri?

536
00:32:58,246 --> 00:32:59,815
Hold it tight.

537
00:32:59,815 --> 00:33:01,650
- Like this?
- Yes.

538
00:33:01,650 --> 00:33:03,085
If I pull too hard,

539
00:33:03,085 --> 00:33:05,287
your eyes will end up
looking narrow and sharp.

540
00:33:05,787 --> 00:33:09,391
You look more handsome with round eyes.

541
00:33:10,092 --> 00:33:10,992
Okay.

542
00:33:12,294 --> 00:33:13,195
Thank you.

543
00:33:15,530 --> 00:33:17,299
When we came here for a picnic before,

544
00:33:17,299 --> 00:33:19,034
it was full of pine trees.

545
00:33:19,968 --> 00:33:21,503
But now it's completely bare.

546
00:33:21,837 --> 00:33:23,905
Do you remember what you told me here
back then?

547
00:33:24,639 --> 00:33:26,208
You said...

548
00:33:26,575 --> 00:33:29,644
your love would stay green all year,
like those pine trees.

549
00:33:30,379 --> 00:33:31,313
But they're gone now.

550
00:33:31,747 --> 00:33:33,148
Who knew...

551
00:33:33,148 --> 00:33:36,952
they'd cut them all down in just a year?

552
00:33:37,619 --> 00:33:40,389
- Exactly.
- Where did they all go?

553
00:33:42,190 --> 00:33:44,659
So this didn't change naturally.

554
00:33:44,659 --> 00:33:46,995
It was cleared all at once
with heavy equipment?

555
00:33:47,929 --> 00:33:50,966
An artificial environmental change
instead of a natural one.

556
00:33:54,803 --> 00:33:55,837
I found it.

557
00:33:56,405 --> 00:33:57,439
What was that?

558
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:01,777
Eureka.

559
00:34:05,514 --> 00:34:06,948
Isn't that Mr. Seong from Mat Story?

560
00:34:07,716 --> 00:34:08,650
Mr. Seong?

561
00:34:15,223 --> 00:34:16,625
What could it be?

562
00:34:18,660 --> 00:34:20,729
Pine trees.

563
00:34:21,363 --> 00:34:24,299
There used to be a pine forest
behind the village, right?

564
00:34:25,033 --> 00:34:27,135
Yes. It was dense
before they cleared it all out.

565
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:29,905
Does that have something
to do with the fungus?

566
00:34:29,905 --> 00:34:31,039
What about the neighboring village?

567
00:34:31,039 --> 00:34:33,075
They didn't cut down their pine trees?

568
00:34:33,075 --> 00:34:35,243
That area wasn't part of
the development project.

569
00:34:35,243 --> 00:34:36,178
What about the pine trees?

570
00:34:36,678 --> 00:34:38,780
It was the pine pollen.

571
00:34:38,780 --> 00:34:41,516
The pollen naturally drifting
from the pine forest...

572
00:34:41,516 --> 00:34:43,185
was acting as a natural disinfectant.

573
00:34:43,552 --> 00:34:46,788
It kept the fungus from growing.

574
00:34:46,788 --> 00:34:48,056
But once the pine trees were cut down,

575
00:34:48,056 --> 00:34:50,058
the fungus spread freely.

576
00:34:50,058 --> 00:34:51,126
My goodness.

577
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:55,130
We destroyed the village's shield
over a bit of money.

578
00:34:58,633 --> 00:35:00,335
We found the cause.

579
00:35:00,335 --> 00:35:01,670
Hurry.

580
00:35:01,670 --> 00:35:02,604
Good work.

581
00:35:02,604 --> 00:35:04,172
Get some rest now.

582
00:35:08,543 --> 00:35:10,078
Hello, sir.

583
00:35:10,345 --> 00:35:11,813
It's me, Ju Hyeong.

584
00:35:11,813 --> 00:35:15,350
You said you have a distant relative
who runs a nursery, right?

585
00:35:15,884 --> 00:35:18,387
Can you ask him if he can gather...

586
00:35:18,387 --> 00:35:20,589
pine resin and pollen for us?

587
00:35:20,589 --> 00:35:21,957
Yes.

588
00:35:21,957 --> 00:35:23,125
All right. Bye.

589
00:35:25,227 --> 00:35:26,661
Hello? It's the Yeonri-ri village chief.

590
00:35:26,661 --> 00:35:27,629
Do you have any pine resin powder?

591
00:35:27,629 --> 00:35:29,865
Everything you can get.
Pine resin, pine trees...

592
00:35:29,865 --> 00:35:31,033
Yes.

593
00:35:31,767 --> 00:35:33,602
Who else is there?

594
00:35:34,736 --> 00:35:35,704
Wow.

595
00:35:37,205 --> 00:35:39,474
Who else is there?

596
00:35:39,841 --> 00:35:42,277
Yeon Su's family. I'll ask them.

597
00:35:44,513 --> 00:35:46,448
It looks like...

598
00:35:46,448 --> 00:35:49,184
she was just trying to educate her kids,

599
00:35:49,184 --> 00:35:51,653
unfairly got scammed,

600
00:35:51,653 --> 00:35:53,388
and took a huge hit.

601
00:35:56,058 --> 00:35:57,426
So, here's what I'm thinking.

602
00:35:57,859 --> 00:36:01,029
We still have money left
in the women's association fund, right?

603
00:36:02,097 --> 00:36:06,468
Let's use that first to put out
the immediate fire.

604
00:36:06,868 --> 00:36:07,903
That's what I propose.

605
00:36:08,236 --> 00:36:09,271
Hey.

606
00:36:09,938 --> 00:36:12,407
Do you know how hard we worked for that?

607
00:36:13,008 --> 00:36:14,876
At the last bazaar,

608
00:36:14,876 --> 00:36:17,579
I was flipping pancakes all day...

609
00:36:17,579 --> 00:36:19,715
and ended up covering my body
with pain patches. Don't you remember?

610
00:36:20,949 --> 00:36:25,020
We saved that for when something big
happens in the village.

611
00:36:25,020 --> 00:36:26,988
If we give it all away at once,

612
00:36:27,622 --> 00:36:29,124
isn't that a problem?

613
00:36:30,292 --> 00:36:31,927
- She's right.
- What will we do?

614
00:36:31,927 --> 00:36:32,994
Right.

615
00:36:33,762 --> 00:36:37,866
Is it such a waste to put food
in a family's mouth?

616
00:36:41,303 --> 00:36:43,105
What's she saying now?

617
00:36:43,472 --> 00:36:46,975
Why are you bringing food
and family into this now?

618
00:36:47,342 --> 00:36:48,910
If she's not family, then what is she?

619
00:36:49,811 --> 00:36:50,712
Ok Rae.

620
00:36:51,279 --> 00:36:55,350
You remember when Mak Rae completely
ruined their field?

621
00:36:55,951 --> 00:36:58,120
What did Mr. Seong do?

622
00:36:59,087 --> 00:37:02,457
He didn't say a word
about his ruined field.

623
00:37:02,457 --> 00:37:04,126
He looked after Mak Rae first.

624
00:37:05,927 --> 00:37:08,764
Yes, I know that too.

625
00:37:09,531 --> 00:37:10,932
What about now?

626
00:37:12,234 --> 00:37:14,202
He's running himself ragged...

627
00:37:14,202 --> 00:37:17,506
trying to save the land.

628
00:37:17,806 --> 00:37:20,242
Is it right for us to just look out
for ourselves like this?

629
00:37:21,209 --> 00:37:24,046
Besides, we're not giving it for free.

630
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:27,482
We're paying back a debt we owe.

631
00:37:30,018 --> 00:37:31,553
You don't think I know that?

632
00:37:32,387 --> 00:37:34,723
I just had to say it.

633
00:37:35,824 --> 00:37:37,626
Since they came to Yeonri-ri,
they're one of us.

634
00:37:37,626 --> 00:37:39,327
They're family now.

635
00:37:40,195 --> 00:37:42,397
You ladies are the best.

636
00:37:44,833 --> 00:37:47,336
But do you think that Mat Story lady...

637
00:37:47,336 --> 00:37:49,905
will just accept the money
if we give it to her?

638
00:37:49,905 --> 00:37:52,341
Shouldn't we have a proper reason?

639
00:37:52,341 --> 00:37:53,942
She won't accept it otherwise.

640
00:37:55,077 --> 00:37:59,848
Since it's for the happiness
of Yeonri-ri people,

641
00:38:00,949 --> 00:38:03,285
we can call it the Happiness Fund.

642
00:38:03,852 --> 00:38:05,520
- Yes.
- That sounds great.

643
00:38:06,888 --> 00:38:09,991
Come on. The Happiness Fund?

644
00:38:09,991 --> 00:38:11,660
Do you have any other ideas?

645
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:13,395
That sounds suspicious.

646
00:38:14,496 --> 00:38:17,032
Then do you have a better idea?

647
00:38:17,499 --> 00:38:18,567
Let's hear it.

648
00:38:18,567 --> 00:38:21,003
There are tons of names for grants.

649
00:38:21,003 --> 00:38:22,938
Just put some words together.

650
00:38:22,938 --> 00:38:23,939
How so?

651
00:38:28,377 --> 00:38:30,312
- Yeonri-ri.
- Yeonri-ri.

652
00:38:30,946 --> 00:38:31,880
Settlement.

653
00:38:32,881 --> 00:38:34,049
Support fund.

654
00:38:34,049 --> 00:38:35,517
Support fund.

655
00:38:35,517 --> 00:38:36,551
Settlement support fund.

656
00:38:36,551 --> 00:38:39,488
Why are you mumbling? I can't hear you.

657
00:38:40,255 --> 00:38:42,324
The Yeonri-ri Settlement Support Fund.

658
00:38:42,324 --> 00:38:43,525
That's perfect.

659
00:38:43,525 --> 00:38:45,627
Just say we forgot to give it
when they first moved here.

660
00:38:45,627 --> 00:38:48,130
That's a great idea.

661
00:38:48,130 --> 00:38:49,798
It's so sophisticated.

662
00:38:49,798 --> 00:38:50,899
Did you just come back from Seoul?

663
00:38:52,401 --> 00:38:54,369
Okay. Talk it through a bit more.

664
00:38:54,369 --> 00:38:55,404
All right.

665
00:39:00,208 --> 00:39:03,545
I love you so much, Nam Hye Sun.

666
00:39:04,813 --> 00:39:06,281
You know my insurance money?

667
00:39:06,581 --> 00:39:09,051
Withdraw $20,000 and transfer it to me.

668
00:39:09,651 --> 00:39:11,186
$20,000? Why?

669
00:39:11,853 --> 00:39:13,255
Is there someone else?

670
00:39:13,255 --> 00:39:14,489
Im Ju Hyeong.

671
00:39:15,190 --> 00:39:16,625
You talk too much.

672
00:39:17,292 --> 00:39:19,528
Do you want to skip dinner starting today?

673
00:39:20,762 --> 00:39:21,930
Just send it.

674
00:39:23,131 --> 00:39:24,266
All right.

675
00:39:28,503 --> 00:39:30,105
Why does she need $20,000?

676
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:33,842
What is it? Is something wrong?

677
00:39:33,842 --> 00:39:36,278
I guess she wants to buy something.

678
00:39:36,978 --> 00:39:38,213
My goodness.

679
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:40,816
You were talking as if...

680
00:39:40,816 --> 00:39:43,685
you'd grab even the stars and moon
for your wife.

681
00:39:43,685 --> 00:39:46,021
Is it something really expensive?

682
00:39:46,988 --> 00:39:49,624
It's not that. It's not me who's paying.

683
00:39:51,860 --> 00:39:53,328
It's my wife's insurance money.

684
00:39:55,497 --> 00:39:56,798
Never mind.

685
00:39:56,798 --> 00:39:59,901
If it's what my Hye Sun wants,
I won't ask any questions.

686
00:40:00,836 --> 00:40:02,437
Will this be enough?

687
00:40:02,838 --> 00:40:06,842
There's no other way
except this natural treatment.

688
00:40:08,443 --> 00:40:10,345
Right. We can't let the land die.

689
00:40:11,013 --> 00:40:12,547
The land is Yeonri-ri's lifeline.

690
00:40:14,249 --> 00:40:17,386
This will suppress the fungus.

691
00:40:26,962 --> 00:40:28,463
What's going on out of the blue?

692
00:40:29,031 --> 00:40:31,166
(Yeonri-ri Village Hall)

693
00:40:34,069 --> 00:40:35,804
- Goodness.
- You're here.

694
00:40:36,905 --> 00:40:39,708
Was there a women's association
meeting today?

695
00:40:39,708 --> 00:40:41,643
You should've told me sooner.

696
00:40:41,643 --> 00:40:43,412
You're here now. That's what matters.

697
00:40:43,412 --> 00:40:44,880
Have a seat.

698
00:40:46,848 --> 00:40:47,783
Hello.

699
00:40:49,818 --> 00:40:51,486
Well...

700
00:40:53,689 --> 00:40:54,589
Here.

701
00:40:59,895 --> 00:41:02,364
Yeonri-ri Settlement Happiness
Support Fund?

702
00:41:04,466 --> 00:41:05,701
What's this?

703
00:41:07,169 --> 00:41:09,905
We should've given this to you
when you first arrived,

704
00:41:09,905 --> 00:41:11,073
but I just forgot.

705
00:41:12,307 --> 00:41:15,110
It's the money we saved up,

706
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:16,411
selling cabbage,

707
00:41:16,411 --> 00:41:19,014
and running bazaars.

708
00:41:22,551 --> 00:41:24,553
Come on.

709
00:41:24,553 --> 00:41:27,456
It's something everyone gets
when they first move here.

710
00:41:27,456 --> 00:41:28,924
Right, Seon Ja?

711
00:41:28,924 --> 00:41:30,258
That's right. I got it too.

712
00:41:31,159 --> 00:41:33,462
That's just how Yeonri-ri is.
Right, sisters?

713
00:41:33,462 --> 00:41:35,230
Right.

714
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:36,231
Everyone gets it.

715
00:41:36,231 --> 00:41:39,334
I've lived here my whole life,

716
00:41:40,369 --> 00:41:44,006
but for this land to have a future,

717
00:41:44,806 --> 00:41:46,875
new people have to come
and put down roots.

718
00:41:47,309 --> 00:41:48,744
That's a great line. Applaud.

719
00:41:52,914 --> 00:41:55,050
Right. That's the New Roots Support Fund.

720
00:41:55,050 --> 00:41:57,953
No, it's the Mak Rae Support Fund.

721
00:41:59,087 --> 00:42:01,390
It's a fund for the happiness
of Yeonri-ri, right?

722
00:42:01,390 --> 00:42:02,891
The Happiness Support Fund.

723
00:42:03,291 --> 00:42:04,693
The official name is...

724
00:42:05,227 --> 00:42:09,364
Yeonri-ri Settlement Happiness
Support Fund.

725
00:42:09,364 --> 00:42:11,133
- Take it.
- No, I can't.

726
00:42:11,133 --> 00:42:13,835
Come on.

727
00:42:13,835 --> 00:42:15,604
Just accept it. I got it too.

728
00:42:15,604 --> 00:42:17,105
Just accept it.

729
00:42:17,105 --> 00:42:18,140
I got it too.

730
00:42:19,408 --> 00:42:20,509
It's okay. Take it.

731
00:42:24,513 --> 00:42:25,614
But...

732
00:42:25,614 --> 00:42:27,716
This is too much.

733
00:42:27,716 --> 00:42:29,718
I can't accept this much.

734
00:42:29,718 --> 00:42:30,986
Come on.

735
00:42:30,986 --> 00:42:32,954
Don't say anything and just take it, okay?

736
00:42:34,056 --> 00:42:36,191
No, I can't.

737
00:42:36,191 --> 00:42:38,694
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

738
00:42:50,305 --> 00:42:51,340
Thank you.

739
00:42:57,212 --> 00:42:58,814
All right. It's late,

740
00:42:59,314 --> 00:43:02,317
but we sincerely congratulate you
on settling in Yeonri-ri.

741
00:43:02,317 --> 00:43:03,352
Applaud.

742
00:43:07,856 --> 00:43:11,059
Welcome to our village.

743
00:43:12,094 --> 00:43:13,428
You're one of us now.

744
00:43:13,428 --> 00:43:15,230
Don't even think about going
anywhere else.

745
00:43:15,697 --> 00:43:16,998
Of course.

746
00:43:16,998 --> 00:43:18,900
We're one family now.

747
00:43:19,201 --> 00:43:22,537
- One family.
- Yes.

748
00:43:29,511 --> 00:43:30,746
Family.

749
00:43:30,746 --> 00:43:33,615
- That's great.
- Family.

750
00:43:34,116 --> 00:43:35,384
We're family.

751
00:43:42,324 --> 00:43:47,529
($31,453 transfer completed
to Kim Hyeon Ju)

752
00:43:56,204 --> 00:43:57,339
The payment's been confirmed.

753
00:44:00,409 --> 00:44:01,309
The debt...

754
00:44:02,210 --> 00:44:03,912
is fully paid now.

755
00:44:03,912 --> 00:44:05,580
All we wanted was our money back.

756
00:44:06,214 --> 00:44:08,950
I hate wasting time getting tangled up
in things like this.

757
00:44:09,851 --> 00:44:11,520
So I hope I never hear from you again.

758
00:44:28,637 --> 00:44:31,273
(A lawsuit to recover a loan)

759
00:44:31,273 --> 00:44:33,008
It's resolved now,

760
00:44:37,846 --> 00:44:39,715
but how will I ever repay this kindness?

761
00:44:47,889 --> 00:44:48,890
Be gentle.

762
00:44:50,225 --> 00:44:51,693
If it gets blown away in the wind,
it'll all be for nothing.

763
00:44:52,828 --> 00:44:53,895
I know.

764
00:44:56,465 --> 00:44:57,432
Goodness.

765
00:44:57,733 --> 00:44:59,768
You're spraying it onto your face
instead of the ground.

766
00:45:01,870 --> 00:45:03,271
Look who's talking.

767
00:45:03,271 --> 00:45:04,473
What?

768
00:45:06,441 --> 00:45:07,275
Is that so?

769
00:45:15,117 --> 00:45:16,184
The fields of Yeonri-ri...

770
00:45:17,819 --> 00:45:19,488
will recover for sure.

771
00:45:22,424 --> 00:45:25,460
A miracle isn't something
that just falls from the sky.

772
00:45:26,695 --> 00:45:28,463
It comes from the hands of the one
who brings the land back to life.

773
00:45:31,933 --> 00:45:32,934
A miracle...

774
00:45:34,703 --> 00:45:36,104
If that miracle happens,

775
00:45:37,639 --> 00:45:39,274
you're much tougher than me.

776
00:45:40,475 --> 00:45:42,477
You're the one who'll save Yeonri-ri
to the end.

777
00:45:42,878 --> 00:45:44,212
I'll give you that, Seong Tae Hun.

778
00:45:47,749 --> 00:45:48,684
You mean that?

779
00:45:49,451 --> 00:45:50,585
If I don't,

780
00:45:51,286 --> 00:45:52,821
would I be out here doing this with you?

781
00:45:57,059 --> 00:45:58,060
Cross.

782
00:46:11,640 --> 00:46:12,407
Here.

783
00:46:13,041 --> 00:46:15,610
I added some honey
to the ginger tea. Drink.

784
00:46:20,115 --> 00:46:21,383
That feels much better.

785
00:46:22,150 --> 00:46:24,720
Pine pollen got into my mouth.

786
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:26,555
I spat it out, but it just kept coming.

787
00:46:31,693 --> 00:46:32,427
Honey.

788
00:46:33,362 --> 00:46:34,229
Is there...

789
00:46:35,597 --> 00:46:37,399
anything I can do for Yeonri-ri?

790
00:46:38,767 --> 00:46:39,735
You?

791
00:46:40,535 --> 00:46:41,603
Why do you ask out of the blue?

792
00:46:41,603 --> 00:46:42,504
Just because...

793
00:46:46,041 --> 00:46:48,477
I received so much kindness...

794
00:46:49,544 --> 00:46:52,381
from the people here.

795
00:46:54,316 --> 00:46:55,617
Honestly,

796
00:46:56,818 --> 00:46:58,653
I thought they'd treat us...

797
00:46:59,554 --> 00:47:01,156
like outsiders...

798
00:47:03,892 --> 00:47:05,460
and push us away.

799
00:47:06,294 --> 00:47:07,562
But I was wrong.

800
00:47:10,365 --> 00:47:13,969
They treat us so well.

801
00:47:17,039 --> 00:47:18,006
I feel the same way.

802
00:47:19,441 --> 00:47:22,010
While you were away,

803
00:47:22,010 --> 00:47:24,012
the village chief and the members
of the women's association...

804
00:47:24,646 --> 00:47:28,116
took turns bringing side dishes every day,

805
00:47:28,450 --> 00:47:29,818
so the kids wouldn't go hungry.

806
00:47:30,952 --> 00:47:31,853
They did?

807
00:47:33,488 --> 00:47:35,924
The things you'd have to pay for
in Seoul...

808
00:47:36,825 --> 00:47:40,862
are just given out of kindness.

809
00:47:47,636 --> 00:47:48,603
I think...

810
00:47:50,539 --> 00:47:52,607
we ended up in a really strange village.

811
00:48:22,871 --> 00:48:23,972
It's coming back to life.

812
00:48:26,308 --> 00:48:27,909
Our field is back to life too.

813
00:48:28,643 --> 00:48:30,379
It's good now.

814
00:48:32,381 --> 00:48:35,117
- We did it.
- It's okay now.

815
00:48:38,453 --> 00:48:39,621
We're good.

816
00:48:41,123 --> 00:48:42,858
We're good.

817
00:48:43,458 --> 00:48:44,893
We're good.

818
00:48:50,298 --> 00:48:51,133
It's back to life.

819
00:48:53,335 --> 00:48:54,269
We did it.

820
00:49:01,143 --> 00:49:02,477
We're good.

821
00:49:03,945 --> 00:49:05,213
We're good.

822
00:49:10,218 --> 00:49:11,219
We're good.

823
00:49:14,322 --> 00:49:15,857
I did it.

824
00:49:16,324 --> 00:49:17,859
Seong Tae Hun and I...

825
00:49:18,727 --> 00:49:21,463
watered it, and sprayed the powder.

826
00:49:22,531 --> 00:49:23,799
Seong Tae Hun and I did it.

827
00:49:25,000 --> 00:49:25,967
I did it.

828
00:49:27,569 --> 00:49:29,004
Seong Tae Hun and I did it.

829
00:49:44,353 --> 00:49:47,456
How could this be? This is great news.

830
00:49:54,496 --> 00:49:57,766
If it weren't for you, we would've been
in big trouble.

831
00:49:58,266 --> 00:49:59,601
We almost plowed everything up...

832
00:49:59,601 --> 00:50:02,637
and ruined the entire year's harvest.

833
00:50:02,637 --> 00:50:06,241
You're the true savior of Yeonri-ri.

834
00:50:07,009 --> 00:50:11,046
If we hadn't listened to him,
who knows what would've happened.

835
00:50:11,046 --> 00:50:12,381
You're right.

836
00:50:12,381 --> 00:50:15,050
We're sorry, and thank you.

837
00:50:15,050 --> 00:50:16,752
I'll treat you with respect from now on.

838
00:50:16,752 --> 00:50:18,487
You're the best.

839
00:50:18,487 --> 00:50:20,155
The best.

840
00:50:20,155 --> 00:50:23,258
Seong Tae Hun.

841
00:50:23,258 --> 00:50:26,495
Seong Tae Hun.

842
00:50:26,495 --> 00:50:29,164
Seong Tae Hun.

843
00:50:29,164 --> 00:50:31,299
You're the best, Mr. Seong.

844
00:50:31,299 --> 00:50:34,236
Seong Tae Hun.

845
00:50:34,236 --> 00:50:35,404
All right.

846
00:50:35,404 --> 00:50:37,072
Settle down, everyone.

847
00:50:37,072 --> 00:50:39,941
Mr. Seong did a great thing for us today,
so we must treat him.

848
00:50:39,941 --> 00:50:42,177
Come over to my place tonight.
Bring the kids too.

849
00:50:42,177 --> 00:50:45,847
Are you cooking an entire cow tonight?

850
00:50:46,314 --> 00:50:48,617
Just a cow? I'll cook a hen too.

851
00:50:49,251 --> 00:50:50,819
Are you ready?

852
00:50:50,819 --> 00:50:52,854
We're ready.

853
00:50:53,922 --> 00:50:54,856
Mr. Seong.

854
00:50:55,157 --> 00:50:56,758
Come hungry tonight.

855
00:51:05,133 --> 00:51:06,168
Thank you, everyone.

856
00:51:08,537 --> 00:51:09,504
Honestly,

857
00:51:11,106 --> 00:51:12,974
I know it wasn't easy...

858
00:51:12,974 --> 00:51:16,278
to trust me and wait.

859
00:51:17,145 --> 00:51:19,748
I'm just an outsider, after all.

860
00:51:20,982 --> 00:51:23,552
Even if it was the chief's request.

861
00:51:25,554 --> 00:51:27,422
You're the one who saved Yeonri-ri's land.

862
00:51:28,090 --> 00:51:29,458
Today, you're the star.

863
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:33,795
I'm saying this loud and clear.

864
00:51:33,795 --> 00:51:35,330
I, Im Ju Hyeong, chose him.

865
00:51:35,330 --> 00:51:37,165
This man is a resident of Yeonri-ri
from now on.

866
00:51:37,165 --> 00:51:38,233
You got that?

867
00:51:38,233 --> 00:51:40,168
Yes.

868
00:51:40,168 --> 00:51:43,238
Seong Tae Hun.

869
00:51:43,238 --> 00:51:46,641
Seong Tae Hun.

870
00:52:15,504 --> 00:52:17,706
Yeonri-ri is a fascinating village.

871
00:52:19,041 --> 00:52:21,376
No matter where you are or what
you're doing, everyone knows everything.

872
00:52:22,244 --> 00:52:23,211
Right.

873
00:52:23,211 --> 00:52:25,414
We probably even know how many spoons
the neighbor has.

874
00:52:26,581 --> 00:52:28,150
So it felt awkward at first.

875
00:52:29,351 --> 00:52:30,585
There was no place to hide.

876
00:52:31,687 --> 00:52:34,423
It can feel unfamiliar and uncomfortable
for people from Seoul.

877
00:52:37,025 --> 00:52:39,928
But these days, I find myself
looking into others first.

878
00:52:41,530 --> 00:52:42,597
Grandma Deok Rae...

879
00:52:43,498 --> 00:52:44,399
gets wrinkles around her eyes...

880
00:52:45,600 --> 00:52:47,202
when she smiles, and she looks so kind.

881
00:52:48,737 --> 00:52:51,073
When Grandma Ok Rae gets angry,

882
00:52:51,073 --> 00:52:52,474
the line between her brows...

883
00:52:52,974 --> 00:52:56,178
is so sharp like it was drawn
with a ruler. It makes her seem lively.

884
00:52:57,179 --> 00:52:58,380
What about Grandma Mak Rae?

885
00:52:59,314 --> 00:53:00,449
Grandma Mak Rae...

886
00:53:01,049 --> 00:53:03,752
When she eats...

887
00:53:03,752 --> 00:53:05,620
and gets food on her face while smiling,

888
00:53:08,323 --> 00:53:09,891
it feels like sunlight spreading.

889
00:53:12,194 --> 00:53:13,862
You really studied them in detail.

890
00:53:15,864 --> 00:53:18,500
Dong Sik from the hardware store
and Seon Ja too.

891
00:53:19,368 --> 00:53:20,635
It's like everyone carves...

892
00:53:22,204 --> 00:53:24,072
their own life into their face.

893
00:53:25,173 --> 00:53:26,575
There's nothing fake about anyone.

894
00:53:28,844 --> 00:53:29,711
But...

895
00:53:30,512 --> 00:53:33,281
among all of them, your face
has the most to look at.

896
00:53:34,850 --> 00:53:36,785
Like how the tip of your nose turns red
when you're cold,

897
00:53:37,986 --> 00:53:39,855
or how your lips tremble slightly
when you talk.

898
00:53:41,923 --> 00:53:44,359
I can't seem to look away from them.

899
00:53:45,560 --> 00:53:48,764
It feels like I'm reading a sentence
that I want to keep just to myself.

900
00:53:51,633 --> 00:53:52,567
What?

901
00:53:53,568 --> 00:53:56,071
What kind of sentence could there be
on a face like mine?

902
00:54:04,513 --> 00:54:06,314
Your hands are warm.

903
00:54:06,314 --> 00:54:07,616
Mine are freezing.

904
00:54:08,383 --> 00:54:10,085
Let me borrow your hand for a moment.

905
00:54:14,322 --> 00:54:16,158
I find your face interesting too.

906
00:54:16,958 --> 00:54:17,826
Do you know?

907
00:54:18,827 --> 00:54:19,861
When...

908
00:54:21,630 --> 00:54:23,365
a book is really good,

909
00:54:23,365 --> 00:54:25,233
the closer you get to the last page,
the more you wish it wouldn't end.

910
00:54:26,935 --> 00:54:28,070
You're like that too.

911
00:54:29,071 --> 00:54:32,741
You're a book I want to read
slowly and savor.

912
00:54:39,214 --> 00:54:40,148
Thanks.

913
00:54:42,951 --> 00:54:44,419
What are you always so grateful about?

914
00:54:45,287 --> 00:54:46,455
Just for your existence.

915
00:54:50,058 --> 00:54:53,362
(MAT STORY)

916
00:54:59,401 --> 00:55:02,237
(Executive Office)

917
00:55:02,237 --> 00:55:03,205
Come in.

918
00:55:07,509 --> 00:55:08,677
Did you call for me, sir?

919
00:55:09,211 --> 00:55:10,979
You're here, Mr. Seong.

920
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:12,814
Have a seat.

921
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:35,237
I think it's time you knew.

922
00:55:39,675 --> 00:55:40,976
We're planning...

923
00:55:42,944 --> 00:55:46,314
to build Mat Story's third factory
on the Yeonri-ri site.

924
00:55:50,886 --> 00:55:52,754
A factory?

925
00:55:53,555 --> 00:55:56,725
It'll be a smart factory, so it won't
even need much manpower.

926
00:55:56,725 --> 00:55:59,227
That land in Yeonri-ri...

927
00:55:59,227 --> 00:56:00,529
is the perfect location.

928
00:56:03,699 --> 00:56:06,568
There are new instructions
from the executive director.

929
00:56:07,402 --> 00:56:08,837
Here in Yeonri-ri,

930
00:56:09,271 --> 00:56:12,708
our company's new vision will take shape.

931
00:56:16,645 --> 00:56:18,914
May I ask about...

932
00:56:19,848 --> 00:56:21,216
the new vision you're planning?

933
00:56:23,185 --> 00:56:24,586
Before I answer that,

934
00:56:25,420 --> 00:56:28,390
I need you to swear
absolute loyalty to me.

935
00:56:29,658 --> 00:56:31,827
I should've realized it then.

936
00:56:33,362 --> 00:56:34,696
Whose heart...

937
00:56:36,698 --> 00:56:39,768
the tip of that pen would
eventually be aimed.

938
00:56:41,937 --> 00:56:42,971
Mr. Seong.

939
00:56:45,273 --> 00:56:46,375
Mr. Seong.

940
00:56:53,949 --> 00:56:56,885
No, sir. We can't build a factory
on that land.

941
00:56:57,652 --> 00:56:58,854
What do you mean, we can't?

942
00:56:59,321 --> 00:57:00,622
The people there...

943
00:57:01,089 --> 00:57:03,859
have lived for generations
trusting that land and farming it.

944
00:57:04,192 --> 00:57:07,195
To them, it's not just land.
It's their livelihood, their life.

945
00:57:07,195 --> 00:57:09,464
I've been there and seen it. I know.

946
00:57:09,464 --> 00:57:10,899
If you build a factory there, they will...

947
00:57:10,899 --> 00:57:11,867
Mr. Seong.

948
00:57:14,503 --> 00:57:17,105
I know you care,

949
00:57:17,806 --> 00:57:19,708
but business isn't run on feelings.

950
00:57:20,809 --> 00:57:22,110
More importantly,

951
00:57:29,217 --> 00:57:32,754
the villagers have already
given their consent.

952
00:57:41,663 --> 00:57:44,066
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

953
00:57:46,368 --> 00:57:47,602
Wait.

954
00:57:47,602 --> 00:57:50,906
This is the list
for the free fertilizer distribution.

955
00:57:50,906 --> 00:57:51,873
I personally...

956
00:57:54,376 --> 00:57:58,580
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

957
00:57:59,181 --> 00:58:01,383
This can't be.

958
00:58:02,084 --> 00:58:03,952
The title should be...

959
00:58:07,389 --> 00:58:09,157
Mr. Bae asked me to pass this along.

960
00:58:10,359 --> 00:58:11,393
He said...

961
00:58:11,393 --> 00:58:13,362
your role in the first task
is extremely important.

962
00:58:14,396 --> 00:58:15,430
First task?

963
00:58:15,864 --> 00:58:19,768
Yeonri-ri residents.
Mat Story is giving away...

964
00:58:19,768 --> 00:58:21,570
premium fertilizer for free.

965
00:58:21,570 --> 00:58:23,205
Yes, it's free. Take as much as you like.

966
00:58:24,940 --> 00:58:25,974
It's okay.

967
00:58:25,974 --> 00:58:28,643
Trust your village chief and take it.

968
00:58:28,643 --> 00:58:30,312
Please sign here.

969
00:58:30,312 --> 00:58:31,713
Please sign.

970
00:58:31,713 --> 00:58:33,081
My good intentions...

971
00:58:33,081 --> 00:58:34,483
(Free fertilizer distribution list
for Yeonri-ri branch)

972
00:58:35,684 --> 00:58:37,185
Right here.

973
00:58:37,185 --> 00:58:38,653
had become the most perfect weapon...

974
00:58:45,894 --> 00:58:49,231
to destroy their lives.

975
00:58:49,231 --> 00:58:51,633
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

976
00:59:03,245 --> 00:59:04,946
You did great work.

977
00:59:05,814 --> 00:59:08,116
It isn't easy to go to each villager...

978
00:59:08,116 --> 00:59:09,985
and collect their signatures.

979
00:59:11,119 --> 00:59:13,789
Thanks to you, construction will go
very smoothly.

980
00:59:20,295 --> 00:59:22,297
Just stay on my side...

981
00:59:22,297 --> 00:59:25,334
and enjoy the result of this list.

982
00:59:27,302 --> 00:59:30,138
I know how country people are.

983
00:59:31,673 --> 00:59:34,476
They talk about being family
and being one,

984
00:59:37,612 --> 00:59:40,282
but the real family you want to protect...

985
00:59:41,583 --> 00:59:42,584
isn't them, right?

986
00:59:53,729 --> 00:59:56,932
A miracle isn't something
that just falls from the sky.

987
00:59:57,866 --> 00:59:59,668
It comes from the hands of the one
who brings the land back to life.

988
01:00:00,469 --> 01:00:01,803
If that miracle happens,

989
01:00:02,571 --> 01:00:04,773
you're the one who'll save Yeonri-ri
to the end.

990
01:00:04,773 --> 01:00:05,774
I'll give you that.

991
01:00:06,742 --> 01:00:07,743
It's coming back to life.

992
01:00:08,877 --> 01:00:11,713
The time limit of the miracle...

993
01:00:12,547 --> 01:00:13,582
was shorter than I expected.

994
01:00:16,018 --> 01:00:18,520
This man is a resident of Yeonri-ri
from now on.

995
01:00:18,520 --> 01:00:21,289
- You got that?
- Yes.

996
01:00:22,591 --> 01:00:26,294
Before the soil I restored
even has time to settle,

997
01:00:28,697 --> 01:00:30,399
I might have to be the one...

998
01:00:33,035 --> 01:00:34,703
to end that miracle myself.

999
01:01:12,074 --> 01:01:15,043
(Cabbage Your Life)

1000
01:01:15,043 --> 01:01:16,144
Didn't you see the news?

1001
01:01:16,144 --> 01:01:18,847
They're building a Mat Story factory
in Yeonri-ri.

1002
01:01:18,847 --> 01:01:19,981
What in the world are you talking about?

1003
01:01:19,981 --> 01:01:21,917
Is the company forcing you to do this?

1004
01:01:21,917 --> 01:01:23,585
This isn't your wrongdoing, is it?

1005
01:01:23,585 --> 01:01:26,488
We'll begin the land acquisition process
starting today.

1006
01:01:26,488 --> 01:01:28,790
Please cooperate in persuading
the villagers.

1007
01:01:28,790 --> 01:01:30,392
Are you really a monster?

1008
01:01:30,392 --> 01:01:33,595
We thought of you as family.
How could you do this to us?

1009
01:01:33,595 --> 01:01:34,663
You should leave.

1010
01:01:34,663 --> 01:01:36,732
It feels uneasy...

1011
01:01:36,732 --> 01:01:39,301
to see everyone including Bo Mi trying
not to make you feel uncomfortable, right?

1012
01:01:39,301 --> 01:01:41,136
You weren't exactly welcomed
from the beginning.

1013
01:01:41,136 --> 01:01:42,704
Just sell your land, Chief.

1014
01:01:42,704 --> 01:01:45,240
Then I won't approach anyone else.

1015
01:01:45,941 --> 01:01:47,943
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

